HEADWORD: Telengiscope
<hw>Te*len"gi*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>th^le</grk> far + <?/ near + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Optics)</fld> <def>An instrument of such focal length that it may
be used as an observing telescope for objects close at hand or as a
long-focused microscope.</def>⟦br⟧
